r Identity at Work        Your Identity at Work  Job Search Resources for Diverse Groups  The Engineering Career Center understands that members of certain groups may experience unique challenges in their job searches. To help, we have compiled this list of both on- campus and off-campus resources. If you are part of a group that's not represented here, or if you know of a great resource that should be listed here, please contact Jonna (Cottrell) McHugh to let her know.       UIC Diversity Portal       Groups     LGBTQIA    UIC Gender and Sexuality Center    Corporate Equality Index - Rating Workplaces on LGBTQ Equality    Transgender in the Workplace    LGBT Connect - Job Board    Out Professionals - LGBT Networking Organization      Veterans/Military    UIC Student Veteran Affairs    My Next Move - tool for exploring civilian careers    Military.com - Job Board    Student Veterans of America - Job Board      DACA/Undocumented    UIC Latino Cultural Center - DACA & Undocumented Student Support    UIC Resources for Undocumented Students    Immigrants Rising Transforming Lives through Education    Applying for an ITIN - Fact Sheet    Employment Rights with DACA      Students With Disabilities    UIC Disability Resource Center    UIC Office for Access and Equity Disability Resources    UIC Disability Cultural Center    Job Accommodation Network    Job Hero - Career Resources for Americans with Disabilities    Job Portal for Persons with Disabilities    Your Rights Under the ADA    HBCU Disability Consortium - What Do I Tell Employers?      First Generation College Students    UIC Office of First Year Initiatives    UIC TRIO Program    Strive For College - online mentor community for first-gen college students          Speak to a Career Advisor  Schedule an Appointment       Need support beyond your job search?          Students/Alum    Back to main content           Search UICcareers.com    Employment Outcomes    International Students & CPT    Your Identity at Work  